  "description_short": "Securityplus is a federally-insured credit union based in Baltimore, MD. Member-owned and not-for-profit, it provides everyday banking, lending, and savings services to its membership.",
  "description_long": "Securityplus is a federal credit union serving members in , , established in 1938. As a not-for-profit financial cooperative, credit unions typically offer lower loan rates, higher savings rates, and fewer fees than traditional banks. This credit union carries a low-income designation, meaning it serves predominantly low-income members and may offer special programs like Payday Alternative Loans (PALs) \u2014 small, affordable loans designed to replace predatory payday lending. The credit union operates 6 branch locations. Deposits are federally insured up to $250,000 by the National Credit Union Administration (NCUA).",
